The weights can be thought of as the inverse of the expected variance of A, and their values can be changed to “tighten” or “loosen” any particular stereochemical restraint. In practice, these variances are used as target values for the observed values of A, and the overall weights on the restraints are varied so as to make the refined structure conform to these target values

